<TEXT>
george bush on monday accused democrat 
michael dukakis of a total lack of understanding of our 
military and called the nov 8 election a referendum on military 
policy 
the vice president used a martinmarietta defense plant where 
star wars research is being conducted to launch his latest 
attack on dukakis 
i will not leave america defenseless against ballistic 
missiles bush told about 2500 company employees in the 
cavernous assembly plant where titan iv rockets are built 
the vice president made the comments before flying to chicago 
where he addressed a jewish group at the holocaust memorial in 
skokie ill bush told his audience that the relationship between 
israel and the united states has never been better never been 
stronger 
at the martinmarietta plant in the foothills of the rocky 
mountains bush ridiculed dukakis for opposing continued ballistic 
missile flight testing 
we need to modernize we need to test and we cant defend 
america with blueprints bush said 
and he scoffed at the democrats position on the reagan 
administrations strategic defense initiative or star wars 
program 
dukakis has been highly critical of the proposed system 
designed to destroy incoming soviet missiles in space but has 
also said during the campaign that he might support some continued 
research 
noting that dukakis had once called the program a fantasy bush 
asked why spend a dime if you think its a fantasy 
attacking dukakis for his opposition to new missile systems and 
for his emphasis on stronger conventional forces has been a main 
bush campaign theme 
bush was planning to introduce that theme in an ad using footage 
of dukakis riding around in a tank during a campaign visit to 
michigan said campaign spokeswoman sheila tate 
although ms tate had no information on a washington post report 
tuesay that the campaign was tentatively planning to spend more 
than 15 million of its 30 millionplus advertising in three 
states she said three new ads were being aired tuesday and a new 
ad was being shot then the three states are california new jersey 
and ohio the post said 
bush declared on monday that with the next century approaching 
it is all that more important for us to understand the role that 
our defense has played in securing the peace the role our military 
forces must continue to play if americas future is also to be 
secure 
and this election is a referendum about that role 
at skokie bush stood in a violent thunderstorm at an outdoor 
rally for the dedication where he said i am committed to the 
survival of israel israel has survived will survive has 
flourished will flourish 
bush talked about the importance of maintaining the strategic 
relationship with israel and joked i wish that the lord had 
given us a little bit of a different weather condition he works in 
strange and mysterious ways 
bush did not mention the controversial effort by the american 
nazi party to hold a march in skokie in 1978 in which the nazis 
were represented by the american civil liberties union the nazis 
decided at the last minute to hold their march in neighboring 
chicago 
bush has frequently criticized dukakis for his membership in the 
aclu aides said the visit should be viewed reinforcement of bushs 
criticism 
with polls showing the vice president pulling ahead of dukakis 
including an nbcwall street journal poll monday showing bush ahead 
5538 republican strategists say bush will focus on a few 
proveneffective themes such as defense in the remaining three 
weeks before the election 
bush donned a bright blue work jacket as he toured the 
martinmarietta plant accompanied by james r schlesinger who has 
served in cabinet jobs in both democratic and republican 
administrations 
the vice president was shown a simulator for a laser weapon 
system to be based on an orbiting space station called rapid 
retargeting precision pointing or by its facetious code name 
r2p2 
bush was told by martinmarietta vice president morris h 
thorson that the device was so accurate that it could hit a 
basketball on top of the empire state building in new york from 
pikes peak in colorado 
schlesinger defense secretary and cia director for president 
ford and energy secretary for president carter told the plant 
employees that the presidency is no place for onthejob 
training 
bush said that the massachusetts governors refusal to back new 
nuclear systems and his willingness to cut two aircraft carriers 
indicates his total lack of understanding of our military 
governor its time to stop running down our defenses bush 
said 
meanwhile bush said he favors a possible mix for a new 
generation of mobile intercontinental ballistic missiles between 
the midgetman missile and a railbased mx missile system but not 
full deployment of both 
dennis ross bushs foreign policy adviser said going ahead 
with both weapons systems would cost some 60 billion and that 
bush wanted to keep the costs of the program to about half that 
