two dartmouth college graduate students 
who were rappelling down steep cliffs were killed after plunging to 
a trail below authorities said today 
they were rappelling down and apparently were both tied to the 
same anchor point and when one fell it broke the point where it 
was tied off said maj henry mock of the state fish and game 
department 
about 50 rescuers worked more than five hours on 4060foot 
cannon mountain to retrieve the bodies of joel sunshine 24 of 
irvine calif and marc fragge 23 of fort mitchell ky mock 
said 
the two were climbing a section of cannon cliffs called beware 
of the dog 
mock said authorities had not determined how far the two fell 
but believe the accident happened at 338 pm sunday because a 
watch strapped to one of the climbers packs was smashed and had 
stopped at that time 
two other climbers who were hiking the trail below cannon cliffs 
found the bodies at 520 pm mock said 
both men were engineering students at dartmouths thayer school 
said dartmouth spokesman rick adams 
