<TEXT>
two sikhs sentenced to death for the 
1984 assassination of prime minister indira gandhi wont be 
executed until the president rules on a petition for mercy news 
reports said monday 
the executions of satwant singh and kehar singh were scheduled 
for oct 19 but will be delayed until president ramaswamy 
venkataraman rules on the mercy plea the united news of india 
reported 
the news agency quoting an unidentified governement spokesman 
said a new date for the executions would be announced if the 
petition is rejected 
the mercy plea was filed by kehar singh 54 but both executions 
will be stayed the agency said satwant singh 24 has refused to 
file a similar plea 
the announcement of the postponement came hours after two courts 
declined to stay the hanging of the two men 
the delhi high court rejected a petition for the stay until 
police investigate a complaint filed by satwant singh that security 
guards shot at him after disarming him following mrs gandhis 
assassination the press trust of india said 
a magistrates court in new delhi another court where satwants 
complain was being heard also rejected a plea to delay the 
execution 
both courts said they had no jurisdiction to stay the hanging 
after it was upheld by the supreme court 
the petition also noted authorities recently arrested a sikh 
terrorist who allegedly helped plan mrs gandhis murder and an 
investigation was pending the report said 
mrs gandhi was shot and killed in the garden of her new delhi 
home on oct 31 1984 by two of her sikh bodyguards satwant singh 
and beant singh 
the two men are not related sikhs by doctrine of their faith 
take the name singh which means lion 
mrs gandhi apparently was murdered in revenge for an army raid 
she ordered four months earlier on the golden temple the sikhs 
holiest shrine in the northern city of amritsar more than 1200 
people died in the attack most of them sikhs 
satwant singh and beant singh were shot by other security guards 
moments after the assassination and beant singh later died of 
bullet wounds 
beant singhs maternal uncle kehar singh was arrested a month 
later and charged with conspiracy in the assassination 
satwant singh and kehar singh were convicted and sentenced to 
death by hanging in january 1986 after an eightmonth trial in new 
delhi 
the delhi high court and the supreme court upheld the 
convictions and death sentences 
the supreme court on aug 3 overturned the death sentence of a 
third man balbir singh ruling there was insufficient evidence to 
prove he participated in the conspiracy 
a district judge wednesday authorized the execution of satwant 
singh and kehar singh who are being held at new delhis 
maximumsecurity tihar central jail 
