<TEXT>
a power outage darkened buildings in 
scattered pockets of downtown when a highvoltage transformer 
failed monday but all electricity was restored within an hour 
officials said 
lights flickered across the salt lake valley when the 
transformer failed at 1023 am mdt but only the downtown area 
lost power said utah power amp light co spokesman dave mead 
the failure of the transformer in a substation blew fuses there 
knocking out power to a second substation and triggering a 
cascade effect in the area he said 
it was not known what caused the failure of the transformer 
which reduces a 12000volt feed to 4000 volts mead said 
power to 90 percent of the area was restored by 1045 with the 
remainder by 1120 am he said 
the transformer remained out of order monday afternoon but utah 
power transferred power feeds to alternate circuits mead said 
