first lady nancy reagan expressed regret 
monday that she failed to heed the advice of white house lawyers 
that she formally disclose her borrowing of gowns and other 
designer apparel but her press secretary and a government ethics 
spokesman said there was no legal requirement that she do so 
press secetary elaine crispen acknowledged that mrs reagan had 
reported such loans when the issue first arose in november 1981 
saying the first lady then decided to err on the side of 
compliance with the law 
since 1982 mrs reagan has continued to borrow and return items 
without reporting the transactions mrs crispen said even though 
white house lawyers originally had recommended disclosure as a 
precautionary measure 
