the communist party chief urged 
yugoslavia on monday to unite behind reform or face destruction 
but a defiant serbian leader defended the mass rallies that are 
fueling ethnic unrest 
worker dissatisfaction over the economy together with ethnic 
discontent have stirred speculation recently about a possible 
military takeover or an eventual breakup of the six republics and 
two autonomous provinces that make up yugoslavia 
defense minister lt gen veljko kadijevic said however it was 
false and malicious to suggest the army should take power 
through a putsch 
the crisis is yugoslavias gravest since world war ii 
a key meeting of the communist partys policysetting central 
