<TEXT>
the pilot of a uganda airlines jet tried three times 
to land in thick fog at romes main airport before the boeing 707 
crashed into houses and trees early monday killing 31 of the 52 
people aboard authorities reported 
the fog a possible misunderstanding between pilot and 
control tower at leonardo da vinci airport and lack of 
sophisticated equipment on a seldomused runway were cited as 
suspected factors in the crash 
all 21 survivors were hospitalized many in critical condition 
with burns fractures and shock only one of seven crew members a 
steward survived 
wreckage was strewn for half a mile but only one injury was 
reported on the ground 
rome police headquarters spokesman paolo moscarelli said late 
monday that one passenger died in a hospital raising the death 
toll to 31 
among survivors was british dairy farmer geoffrey gait who said 
he and his wife ruth who was holding their 8monthold son jumped 
from the wreckage right before it went up in flames the family 
suffered slight burns 
the jet missed the runway by several hundred yards it tore 
through a wooden house clipped a garage demolished a brick house 
under construction and plowed through the parking lot of a car 
rental agency where an engine and a wing tore off and a fire 
destroyed 75 cars according to authorities 
an occupant of the wooden house carlo satta 30 was hit on the 
nose by a beam as he slept in bed in fiumicino 21 miles southwest 
of rome 
flight no 775 began at londons gatwick airport late sunday and 
was bound for entebbe uganda with a onehour stopover scheduled 
in rome 
most of those aboard were ugandans the british embassy in rome 
said the passenger list included seven or eight british citizens 
two nigerians were listed among the injured 
airport authorities said monday evening they did not have a list 
of the dead by name and nationality 
alberto di giulio head of the national flight safety office 
said the jet tried to land three times at the seaside airport 
before it crashed 
passenger john harigye a former ugandan ambassador to the 
vatican told reporters from his hospital bed that a flight 
attendant told him just before the crash that the plane tried once 
to land had to circle because of the fog and was about to try 
another landing 
he said that next came a violent collision and he found himself 
upside down in his seat held by his seatbelt 
i realized one side of the plane was gone i pushed through a 
hole helping a family friend seated near him to leave the plane 
he said 
outside the jet i saw a woman who was calling me she knew 
me i told her to move away then the plane exploded said 
harigye whose hand bandage was soaked with blood the fuel 
apparently ignited after the crash 
guido chiucini commander of rome provinces fire department 
speculated in a telephone interview that a misunderstanding may 
have developed between the control tower and the pilot since the 
landing was begun at a very low altitude 
chiucini who helped coordinate the rescue did not elaborate 
later the air traffic controllers union denied there was a 
misunderstanding 
asked about chiucinis remarks di giulio said the tapes of 
cockpit conversation had yet to be reviewed 
since sunday evening a heavy fog had enveloped the rome 
seacoast including the airport 
the fog appears to have been the main culprit di giulio 
said 
without citing its sources rai state television said the pilot 
began the third attempt too low italys ansa news agency said the 
pilot had approached from three different directions because of 
shifting fog banks 
andrea gariup of italys main pilots union was quoted by rai 
as saying the runway on which the pilot tried to land lacked 
sophisticated equipment to help in instrument landings and was not 
normally used 
authorities reported both the flight instrument data recordings 
and the recordings of conversations between cockpit and tower were 
recovered 
gait said he was involved in a charity project to provide uganda 
farmers with cows 
