<TEXT>
a malfunctioning fan in a 
plutoniumprocessing area caused the evacuation of about 100 
employees at the savannah river plant monday but officials said 
there was no contamination of the workers or the atmosphere 
the fan broke down at 246 pm and was restarted about 30 
minutes later said plant spokesman cliff webb the cause of the 
equipment failure was under investigation 
the exhaust fan is used to pull fresh air from the outside 
through the building and out to filters that trap any radioactive 
material the air flow serves to remove any releases of 
contamination from the building 
but a fan failure could produce a reverse air flow which could 
allow contamination to accumulate in the building or be forced 
outside 
the amount of contamination would depend on how much plutonium 
was being processed when such an accident occurred officials will 
not discuss specifics on plutonium production 
a backup fan normally would have been activated but the second 
unit was out of service for routine maintenance webb said 
meanwhile about 700 employees elsewhere in farea where 
plutonium is refined for use in nuclear weapons were detained 
about an hour while an inventory of nuclear materials was 
completed such inventories are routinely conducted webb said 
