claras heart 
 
clara mayfield is a brutally direct woman who colors her human 
relationships with a good deal of common sense selfrighteousness 
and tenacity she also has an overwhelming humanity about her and 
that specialness attracts people to her like a magnet 
the relationship she forges with young david hart is bound to be 
a memorable screen joining 
clara is a vibrant and rich role one that could easily turn 
around whoopi goldbergs dismal film career after such losers as 
burglarjumpin jack flash and fatal beauty in which 
the standup comic was required to do little more than imitate 
eddie murphy and be the butterfly mcqueen of the 1980s goldberg 
finally has a chance to demonstrate her talents as a dramatic 
actress 
robert mulligan to kill a mockingbirdinside daisy 
clover restrains goldberg in his direction of this family 
melodrama allowing none of the bits and business that have become 
the trademarks of her wealth of comic stage characters that 
restraint is essential to clara herself a jamaican with a dark 
secret 
clara enters the lives of the affluent hart family from 
marylands eastern shore shortly after the crib death of their 
daughter leona kathleen quinlan and bill michaelontkean have 
gone to jamaica to help get over the tragedy clara is their hotel 
maid 
she coaxes leona out of her depression and encourages her to get 
on with life leona decides to bring her back to maryland she 
cant quite function without claras island sensibilities but son 
david hart takes an immediate dislike to clara and accuses his 
parents rightfully so of bringing her home so they wont have 
to deal with him 
the harts are in the process of a divorce he has taken up with 
a hot cutie and she has taken up with a pretentious bore of a pop 
shrink spalding gray 
clara eventually wins over david to the point where hed rather 
spend his weekends in baltimore with clara and her west indian 
friends than with his parents he also picks up claras island 
patois to the delight of her friends 
but davids dependency on clara ultimately leads to her dark 
revelation and it is here that the movie falters there is no 
buildup to this awful experience in her life and its unfolding is 
an abrupt twist and with the tale there remain loose ends 
letters hidden in a suitcase and found by david are never 
explained the father of claras child also is a mystery 
still claras heart is a warm movie with many lessons to 
tell if one is willing to listen its force is aided by goldbergs 
performance and a noteworthy movie debut of neil patrick harris as 
david 
the warner bros release of an mtm entertainment production 
features a lilting score by dave grusin but hollywood has yet to 
learn through its endless quest for authenticity that steel music 
and calypso are products of trinidad not jamaica where reggae and 
soca bloom 
martin elfand produced claras heart which is rated pg13 
by dolores barclay ap arts editor 
</TEXT>
