imagine john lennon 
 
rarely has a 20thcentury phenomenon been so thoroughly 
chronicled in every conceivable way as the beatles 
yet the new documentary imagine john lennon provides 
previously unseen material on the most enigmatic of the beatles if 
not any fresh insights 
yoko ono lennons everprotective widow released 200 hours of 
tapes and films from their private collection to documentary and 
miniseries producer david l wolper the making of the president 
1960roots wolper and producerdirector andrew solt culled 
through the material and also searched for newsreels and tv 
appearances 
the documentary material was combined with new interviews with 
yoko ono and lennons first wife cynthia sons julian and sean 
and various associates of lennon none of the three surviving 
beatles was interviewed 
imagine provides a gold mine for beatle lovers and 
especially those who revere lennon who was slain outside his 
apartment in manhattan by a crazed fan in 1980 
but the film provides marginal entertainment for the average 
moviegoer documentaries are never easy to endure in a theater 
imagine is no exception despite the great skill that went into 
its making 
there are some riveting moments the most scarifying comes when 
john and yoko encounter cartoonist al capp lil abner during 
the montreal bedin for peace a meeting as deadly in its way as a 
mongooses minuet with two cobras 
the lennons penchant for shock is demonstrated in a nude 
lovemaking scene which was filmed two weeks before he died 
intended for a music video it is antiseptically graphic hardly 
erotic at all 
director solt has capably maintained the kind of pace 
established in the trendsetting beatles feature a hard days 
night only in the final sequence does the film falter lennons 
murder and the outpouring of grief from his candleholding fans is 
protracted into a kind of deification that hardly suits the subject 
there is commentary by family and friends and lennons own 
voice narrates much of imagine whether he was excessively 
narcissistic or merely had a exceptional sense of history 
posterity should be grateful for his extensive recordkeeping how 
valuable it would be to have such records of james dean marilyn 
monroe elvis presley and other icons 
the warner bros release was coproduced by sam egan and written 
by egan and solt rated r for nudity and language running time 
103 minutes 
by bob thomas associated press writer 
