arthur andersen amp co the largest accounting 
firm in the nation announced a new name for its lucrative 
consulting division monday in a move thought to be prompted by 
concerns over ethics and personnel 
the change in the divisions name from us management 
information consulting to andersen consulting creates a clear 
separate identity said duane r kullberg managing partner and 
chief executive officer of the chicagobased company 
andersens consulting service helps businesses tailor computer 
systems to their specific needs 
andersen launched a study last month to consider a possible 
restructuring of the entire company which some observers believe 
may be a prelude to splitting off consulting as an independent 
business 
the growth of consulting services at major accounting firms has 
raised questions about the ethics of supposedly objective 
accounting companies advising their clients on managerial decisions 
some experts have said the ethical problems can only be solved 
by splitting off consulting as a separate business 
consultants at accounting firms complain that although they are 
responsible for much of their firms revenue growth they are 
treated and paid as secondclass citizens by managing partners who 
came up through the tax and audit business 
the rift has cost andersen some of its top consulting partners 
including four who quit on friday to join a new consulting venture 
the consulting arm of arthur andersen accounts for about 40 
percent of the companys total revenue and is growing at a rate of 
about 30 percent a year officials said 
consulting fees are expected to total more than 13 billion at 
privately held andersen this year compared with 17 billion in 
revenue from the companys tax and audit portion 
