investments in real estate and in oil and gas it charged the 
company then overstated the value of its remaining operations 
although the pittsburghbased conglomerate realized more than 
500 million from the sales the money representated far less 
than their real market value according to the lawsuit 
the lawsuit also charged that a march 1987 tender offer by a 
subsidiary of the investment banking firm first boston inc of new 
york relied on inflated projections of allegheny internationals 
performance 
spear leeds amp kellogg purchased additional shares of allegheny 
international stock based on the projections according to the 
lawsuit 
the lawsuit charged that the true financial state of the company 
was reflected in allegheny internationals announcement that it has 
lost 2854 million for the fiscal year ending sept 27 1987 
allegheny international spokesman edward romanoff declined 
comment on the lawsuit 
allegheny international sought protection under chapter 11 of 
federal bankruptcy laws in february the company manufactures 
sunbeam and oster products among others 
</TEXT>
